# Dynasty Empire — SuiteDash Deployment System
# Cursor IDE Instructions

## Project Overview
Multi-niche directory business factory powered by SuiteDash (CRM/portal), n8n (automation), AiTable (data/analytics), and Stripe (payments). 16 niches, 7 AI agents, 9 n8n workflows, 12 AiTable tables.

## Architecture
- **SuiteDash** = Client portal, identity, billing (manual config via web UI)
- **n8n** = Automation orchestration (9 importable JSON workflows)
- **AiTable** = Data layer, analytics, agent memory (12 tables)
- **Stripe** = Payment processing (webhooks only)
- **OpenAI** = Agent intelligence (GPT-4 via n8n HTTP nodes)

## Key Files
- `env/.env` — All API credentials (NEVER commit to git)
- `n8n/*.json` — Importable n8n workflow definitions (import via n8n UI or API)
- `suitedash/` — Configuration references for manual SuiteDash setup
- `scripts/` — Node.js setup/deployment/testing utilities
- `dashboard/` — Operations monitoring dashboard (static HTML + Chart.js)
- `data/` — CSV schemas for AiTable table creation

## API Patterns

### SuiteDash API
- Base URL: `https://portal.yourdeputy.com/secure-api`
- Auth: Headers `X-Public-ID: {SUITEDASH_API_ID}` and `X-Secret-Key: {SUITEDASH_API_SECRET}` (see Integrations → Secure API; not X-API-KEY)
- Endpoints: /contact, /contacts, /company, /companies, /invoice, /invoices, /project, /projects, /deal, /deals, /task, /tasks, /pipeline, /pipelines, /circle, /circles
- Rate limits: Start=400/mo, Thrive=2000/mo, Pinnacle=20000/mo
- CRITICAL: Always check API rate limits before batch operations

### AiTable API
- Base URL: `https://aitable.ai/fusion/v1/datasheets/{TABLE_ID}`
- Auth: Header `Authorization: Bearer {AITABLE_API_KEY}`
- Key: `usk8wYBrRgsc6RHxkZP9VAN`
- Operations: GET (list records), POST (create), PATCH (update), DELETE
- This is AiTable, NOT Airtable — different API format

### n8n API
- Base URL: Configured via N8N_BASE_URL
- Auth: Header `X-N8N-API-KEY` + Cloudflare Access headers
- Webhook base: `{N8N_WEBHOOK_BASE}/dynasty-events` (Master Event Router)

## Conventions
- All n8n workflows check Emergency Stop (AiTable system_config) before executing
- All workflows use Pack 5 (failure_handler) as their error workflow
- All events route through Pack 8 (master_event_router) — single webhook endpoint
- Engagement Score formula: (Logins×2) + (ProfileUpdates×3) + (Features×1) + (CommunityPosts×2) + (Tickets×5) - (DaysSinceLogin×1)
- Circle naming: `{NicheName}-{Tier}` (e.g., "Plumbing-Premium")
- Lead scoring: Urgency(25) + Budget(25) + Location(20) + Size(15) + Completeness(15) = 100

## 16 Niches (in deployment order)
1. Plumbing, 2. HVAC, 3. Pest Control, 4. Roofing, 5. Real Estate, 6. Property Management,
7. Immigration Legal, 8. Tax & Accounting, 9. Medical Billing, 10. Home Cleaning,
11. Landscaping, 12. Auto Repair, 13. Childcare, 14. Fitness Coaches,
15. Digital Marketing, 16. Construction

## Do NOT
- Use Airtable APIs — this project uses AiTable (different service)
- Push .env files to git
- Modify n8n workflow JSONs without testing import first
- Exceed SuiteDash API rate limits (track in system_config)
- Send customer-facing emails outside 8am-8pm local time
- Run destructive operations without Emergency Stop check

